                  arc_data_r PROC
;;;1378   
;;;1379       static int arc_data_r(                        /* ARGUMENTS                                     */
000000  e92d5fff          PUSH     {r0-r12,lr}
;;;1380       int move,                                     /* either G_2 (cw arc) or G_3 (ccw arc)          */
;;;1381       double current_x,                             /* first coordinate of current point             */
;;;1382       double current_y,                             /* second coordinate of current point            */

;;;1384       double end_y,                                 /* second coordinate of arc end point            */

;;;1386       double * center_x,                            /* pointer to first coordinate of center of arc  */
;;;1387       double * center_y,                            /* pointer to second coordinate of center of arc */

                  convert_arc PROC
;;;1865   
;;;1866       static int convert_arc(                       /* ARGUMENTS                                */
000000  e92d4ff0          PUSH     {r4-r11,lr}
;;;1867       int move,                                     /* either G_2 (cw arc) or G_3 (ccw arc)     */
;;;1868       block_pointer block,                          /* pointer to a block of RS274 instructions */
;;;1869       setup_pointer settings)                       /* pointer to machine settings              */

;;;1873           int first;                                /* flag set ON if this is first move after comp ON */
;;;1874           int ijk_flag;                             /* flag set ON if any of i,j,k present in NC code  */

;;;1876           double end_y;
;;;1877           double end_z;

;;;1883   #endif
;;;1884   #ifdef CC

;;;1886   #endif

                  |L10.30|

                  |L10.36|

                  |L10.40|

00002a  f5054130          ADD      r1,r5,#0xb000
00002e  f50171bc          ADD      r1,r1,#0x178

                  |L10.166|
;;;1893               NCE_R_I_J_K_WORDS_ALL_MISSING_FOR_ARC);
;;;1894           CHK(((block->r_flag IS ON) AND (ijk_flag IS ON)),
;;;1895               NCE_MIXED_RADIUS_IJK_FORMAT_FOR_ARC);
;;;1896           if (settings->feed_mode IS UNITS_PER_MINUTE)
;;;1897           {
;;;1898               CHK((settings->feed_rate IS 0.0),
;;;1899                   NCE_CANNOT_MAKE_ARC_WITH_ZERO_FEED_RATE);
;;;1900           }
;;;1901           else if (settings->feed_mode IS INVERSE_TIME)
;;;1902           {
;;;1903               CHK((block->f_number IS -1.0),
;;;1904                   NCE_F_WORD_MISSING_WITH_INVERSE_TIME_ARC_MOVE);
;;;1905           }
;;;1906           if (ijk_flag)
;;;1907           {
;;;1908               if (settings->plane IS CANON_PLANE_XY)
;;;1909               {
;;;1910                   CHK((block->k_flag), NCE_K_WORD_GIVEN_FOR_ARC_IN_XY_PLANE);
;;;1911                   if (block->i_flag IS OFF)         /* i or j flag on to get here */
;;;1912                       block->i_number SET_TO 0.0;
;;;1913                   else if (block->j_flag IS OFF)
;;;1914                       block->j_number SET_TO 0.0;
;;;1915               }
;;;1916               else if (settings->plane IS CANON_PLANE_YZ)
;;;1917               {
;;;1918                   CHK((block->i_flag), NCE_I_WORD_GIVEN_FOR_ARC_IN_YZ_PLANE);
;;;1919                   if (block->j_flag IS OFF)         /* j or k flag on to get here */
;;;1920                       block->j_number SET_TO 0.0;
;;;1921                   else if (block->k_flag IS OFF)
;;;1922                       block->k_number SET_TO 0.0;
;;;1923               }
;;;1924               else if (settings->plane IS CANON_PLANE_XZ)
;;;1925               {
;;;1926                   CHK((block->j_flag), NCE_J_WORD_GIVEN_FOR_ARC_IN_XZ_PLANE);
;;;1927                   if (block->i_flag IS OFF)         /* i or k flag on to get here */
;;;1928                       block->i_number SET_TO 0.0;
;;;1929                   else if (block->k_flag IS OFF)
;;;1930                       block->k_number SET_TO 0.0;
;;;1931               }
;;;1932               else
;;;1933                   ERM(NCE_BUG_PLANE_NOT_XY_YZ_OR_XZ);
;;;1934           }
;;;1935           else;                                     /* r format arc; no other checks needed specific to this format */
;;;1936   
;;;1937           if (settings->plane IS CANON_PLANE_XY)    /* checks for both formats */
;;;1938            {
;;;1939               CHK(((block->x_flag IS OFF) AND (block->y_flag IS OFF)),
;;;1940                   NCE_X_AND_Y_WORDS_MISSING_FOR_ARC_IN_XY_PLANE);
;;;1941           }
;;;1942           else if (settings->plane IS CANON_PLANE_YZ)
;;;1943           {
;;;1944               CHK(((block->y_flag IS OFF) AND (block->z_flag IS OFF)),
;;;1945                   NCE_Y_AND_Z_WORDS_MISSING_FOR_ARC_IN_YZ_PLANE);
;;;1946           }
;;;1947           else if (settings->plane IS CANON_PLANE_XZ)
;;;1948           {
;;;1949               CHK(((block->x_flag IS OFF) AND (block->z_flag IS OFF)),
;;;1950                   NCE_X_AND_Z_WORDS_MISSING_FOR_ARC_IN_XZ_PLANE);
;;;1951           }
;;;1952   
;;;1953           find_ends(block, settings, &end_x, &end_y,
;;;1954               &end_z
;;;1955       #ifdef AA
;;;1956               , &AA_end
;;;1957       #endif
;;;1958   
;;;1959       #ifdef BB
;;;1960               , &BB_end
;;;1961       #endif
;;;1962   
;;;1963       #ifdef CC
;;;1964               , &CC_end
;;;1965       #endif
;;;1966               );

;;;2215   
;;;2216       static int convert_arc_comp1(                 /* ARGUMENTS                                   */

;;;2252               NCE_CUTTER_GOUGING_WITH_CUTTER_RADIUS_COMP);
;;;2253   
;;;2254           if (block->r_flag)

                          AREA ||i.convert_arc_comp2||, CODE, READONLY, ALIGN=2

                  convert_arc_comp2 PROC
;;;2363   
;;;2364       static int convert_arc_comp2(                 /* ARGUMENTS                                 */
000000  e92d4fff          PUSH     {r0-r11,lr}
;;;2365       int move,                                     /* either G_2 (cw arc) or G_3 (ccw arc)           */
;;;2366       block_pointer block,                          /* pointer to a block of RS274/NGC instructions   */
;;;2367       setup_pointer settings,                       /* pointer to machine settings                    */
;;;2368       double end_x,                                 /* x-value at end of programmed (then actual) arc */
;;;2369       double end_y,                                 /* y-value at end of programmed (then actual) arc */
;;;2370       double end_z                                  /* z-value at end of arc                          */
;;;2371   #ifdef AA
;;;2372       , double AA_end                               /* a-value at end of arc                    *//*AA*/
;;;2373   #endif
;;;2374   #ifdef BB
;;;2375       , double BB_end                               /* b-value at end of arc                    *//*BB*/
;;;2376   #endif
;;;2377   #ifdef CC
;;;2378       , double CC_end                               /* c-value at end of arc                    *//*CC*/
;;;2379   #endif
;;;2380       )
;;;2381       {
000004  b0b7              SUB      sp,sp,#0xdc
000006  4616              MOV      r6,r2
000008  ac44              ADD      r4,sp,#0x110
00000a  e89407b0          LDM      r4,{r4,r5,r7-r10}
;;;2382           static char name[] SET_TO "convert_arc_comp2";
;;;2383           double alpha;                             /* direction of tangent to start of arc */
;;;2384           double arc_radius;
;;;2385           double beta;                              /* angle between two tangents above */
;;;2386           double center_x;                          /* center of arc */
;;;2387           double center_y;
;;;2388           double delta;                             /* direction of radius from start of arc to center of arc */
;;;2389           double gamma;                             /* direction of perpendicular to arc at end */
;;;2390           double mid_x;
;;;2391           double mid_y;
;;;2392           int side;
;;;2393      /* angle for testing corners */
;;;2394           double small SET_TO TOLERANCE_CONCAVE_CORNER;
00000e  49ff              LDR      r1,|L13.1036|
000010  48ff              LDR      r0,|L13.1040|
000012  e9cd1022          STRD     r1,r0,[sp,#0x88]
;;;2395           double start_x;
;;;2396           double start_y;
;;;2397           int status;                               /* status returned from CHP function call     */
;;;2398           double theta;                             /* direction of tangent to last cut */
;;;2399           double tolerance;
;;;2400           double tool_radius;
;;;2401           int turn;                                 /* number of full or partial circles CCW */
;;;2402   
;;;2403      /* find basic arc data: center_x, center_y, and turn */
;;;2404   
;;;2405           start_x SET_TO settings->program_x;
000016  f5064130          ADD      r1,r6,#0xb000
00001a  f50171bc          ADD      r1,r1,#0x178
00001e  c903              LDM      r1,{r0,r1}
000020  e9cd0120          STRD     r0,r1,[sp,#0x80]
;;;2406           start_y SET_TO settings->program_y;
000024  f5064030          ADD      r0,r6,#0xb000
000028  f50070c0          ADD      r0,r0,#0x180

                  convert_cycle_g81 PROC
;;;3529   
;;;3530       static int convert_cycle_g81(                 /* ARGUMENTS                        */
000000  e92d5fff          PUSH     {r0-r12,lr}
;;;3531       CANON_PLANE plane,                            /* selected plane                   */
;;;3532       double x,                                     /* x-value where cycle is executed  */
;;;3533       double y,                                     /* y-value where cycle is executed  */
;;;3534       double clear_z,                               /* z-value of clearance plane       */
;;;3535       double bottom_z)                              /* value of z at bottom of cycle    */
;;;3536       {

000006  4616              MOV      r6,r2
000008  461f              MOV      r7,r3
00000a  ac12              ADD      r4,sp,#0x48
00000c  e8940f30          LDM      r4,{r4,r5,r8-r11}
;;;3537   //        static char name[] SET_TO "convert_cycle_g81";
;;;3538   
;;;3539           cycle_feed(plane, x, y, bottom_z);
000010  4632              MOV      r2,r6
000012  463b              MOV      r3,r7
000014  e88d0c30          STM      sp,{r4,r5,r10,r11}
000018  9804              LDR      r0,[sp,#0x10]
00001a  f7fffffe          BL       cycle_feed
;;;3540           cycle_traverse(plane, x, y, clear_z);

000020  463b              MOV      r3,r7
000022  e88d0330          STM      sp,{r4,r5,r8,r9}
000026  9804              LDR      r0,[sp,#0x10]
000028  f7fffffe          BL       cycle_traverse
;;;3541   
;;;3542           return RS274NGC_OK;
00002c  2000              MOVS     r0,#0
;;;3543       }
00002e  b008              ADD      sp,sp,#0x20
000030  e8bd9ff0          POP      {r4-r12,pc}
;;;3544   
                          ENDP

                  convert_cycle_g83 PROC
;;;3622   
;;;3623       static int convert_cycle_g83(                 /* ARGUMENTS                        */
000000  e92d5fff          PUSH     {r0-r12,lr}

;;;3646               cycle_traverse(plane, x, y, current_depth + rapid_delta);

000076  464b              MOV      r3,r9

                  convert_cycle_g89 PROC
;;;3992   
;;;3993       static int convert_cycle_g89(                 /* ARGUMENTS                        */
000000  e92d5fff          PUSH     {r0-r12,lr}
;;;3994       CANON_PLANE plane,                            /* selected plane                   */
;;;3995       double x,                                     /* x-value where cycle is executed  */
;;;3996       double y,                                     /* y-value where cycle is executed  */
;;;3997       double clear_z,                               /* z-value of clearance plane       */
;;;3998       double bottom_z,                              /* value of z at bottom of cycle    */
;;;3999       double dwell)                                 /* dwell time                       */
;;;4000       {
000004  b084              SUB      sp,sp,#0x10
000006  4616              MOV      r6,r2
000008  461f              MOV      r7,r3
00000a  ac12              ADD      r4,sp,#0x48
00000c  e8940f30          LDM      r4,{r4,r5,r8-r11}
;;;4001   //        static char name[] SET_TO "convert_cycle_g89";
;;;4002   
;;;4003           cycle_feed(plane, x, y, bottom_z);
000010  4632              MOV      r2,r6
000012  463b              MOV      r3,r7

000018  9804              LDR      r0,[sp,#0x10]

;;;4004           DWELL(dwell);
00001e  e9dd0118          LDRD     r0,r1,[sp,#0x60]

;;;4005           cycle_feed(plane, x, y, clear_z);

000028  463b              MOV      r3,r7

00002e  9804              LDR      r0,[sp,#0x10]

;;;4006   
;;;4007           return RS274NGC_OK;
000034  2000              MOVS     r0,#0
;;;4008       }
000036  b008              ADD      sp,sp,#0x20
000038  e8bd9ff0          POP      {r4-r12,pc}
;;;4009

                  convert_cycle_xy PROC
;;;4126   
;;;4127           static int convert_cycle_xy(              /* ARGUMENTS                                 */

                  |L31.104|
;;;4153                   NCE_Z_VALUE_UNSPECIFIED_IN_XY_PLANE_CANNED_CYCLE);
;;;4154           }
;;;4155           block->z_number SET_TO
;;;4156               block->z_flag IS ON ? block->z_number : settings->cycle_cc;
;;;4157           old_cc SET_TO settings->current_z;
;;;4158   
;;;4159           if (settings->distance_mode IS MODE_ABSOLUTE)
;;;4160           {
;;;4161               aa_increment SET_TO 0.0;
;;;4162               bb_increment SET_TO 0.0;
;;;4163               r SET_TO block->r_number;
;;;4164               cc SET_TO block->z_number;
;;;4165               aa SET_TO block->x_flag IS ON ? block->x_number : settings->current_x;
;;;4166               bb SET_TO block->y_flag IS ON ? block->y_number : settings->current_y;
;;;4167           }
;;;4168           else if (settings->distance_mode IS MODE_INCREMENTAL)
;;;4169           {
;;;4170               aa_increment SET_TO block->x_number;
;;;4171               bb_increment SET_TO block->y_number;
;;;4172               r SET_TO (block->r_number + old_cc);
;;;4173               cc SET_TO (r + block->z_number);      /* [NCMS, page 98] */
;;;4174               aa SET_TO settings->current_x;
;;;4175               bb SET_TO settings->current_y;
;;;4176           }
;;;4177           else
;;;4178               ERM(NCE_BUG_DISTANCE_MODE_NOT_G90_OR_G91);
;;;4179           CHK((r < cc), NCE_R_LESS_THAN_Z_IN_CYCLE_IN_XY_PLANE);
;;;4180   
;;;4181           if (old_cc < r)
;;;4182           {
;;;4183               STRAIGHT_TRAVERSE(settings->current_x, settings->current_y, r
;;;4184       #ifdef AA
;;;4185                   ,     settings->AA_current
;;;4186       #else
;;;4187       #ifdef ALL_AXES
;;;4188                   , 0
;;;4189       #endif
;;;4190       #endif
;;;4191       #ifdef BB
;;;4192                   ,  settings->BB_current
;;;4193       #else
;;;4194       #ifdef ALL_AXES
;;;4195                   , 0
;;;4196       #endif
;;;4197       #endif

;;;4199                   ,  settings->CC_current
;;;4200       #else
;;;4201       #ifdef ALL_AXES
;;;4202                   , 0
;;;4203       #endif
;;;4204       #endif
;;;4205                   );
;;;4206               old_cc SET_TO r;
;;;4207           }
;;;4208           clear_cc SET_TO (settings->retract_mode IS R_PLANE) ? r : old_cc;
;;;4209   
;;;4210           save_mode SET_TO GET_EXTERNAL_MOTION_CONTROL_MODE();
;;;4211           if (save_mode ISNT CANON_EXACT_PATH)
;;;4212               SET_MOTION_CONTROL_MODE(CANON_EXACT_PATH);
;;;4213   
;;;4214           switch(motion)
;;;4215           {
;;;4216               case G_81:
;;;4217                   CYCLE_MACRO(convert_cycle_g81(CANON_PLANE_XY, aa, bb, clear_cc, cc))

;;;4219               case G_82:

;;;4223                       block->p_number IS -1.0 ? settings->cycle_p : block->p_number;

;;;4226                       settings->cycle_p SET_TO block->p_number;

;;;4228               case G_83:

;;;4232                       block->q_number IS -1.0 ? settings->cycle_q : block->q_number;
;;;4233                   CYCLE_MACRO(convert_cycle_g83 (CANON_PLANE_XY, aa, bb, r, clear_cc, cc,
;;;4234                       block->q_number))
;;;4235                       settings->cycle_q SET_TO block->q_number;
;;;4236                   break;
;;;4237               case G_84:
;;;4238                   CYCLE_MACRO(convert_cycle_g84 (CANON_PLANE_XY, aa, bb, clear_cc, cc,
;;;4239                       settings->spindle_turning, settings->speed_feed_mode))
;;;4240                       break;
;;;4241               case G_85:
;;;4242                   CYCLE_MACRO(convert_cycle_g85 (CANON_PLANE_XY, aa, bb, clear_cc, cc))
;;;4243                       break;
;;;4244               case G_86:
;;;4245                   CHK(((settings->motion_mode ISNT G_86) AND (block->p_number IS -1.0)),
;;;4246                       NCE_DWELL_TIME_P_WORD_MISSING_WITH_G86);
;;;4247                   block->p_number SET_TO
;;;4248                       block->p_number IS -1.0 ? settings->cycle_p : block->p_number;
;;;4249                   CYCLE_MACRO(convert_cycle_g86 (CANON_PLANE_XY, aa, bb, clear_cc, cc,
;;;4250                       block->p_number, settings->spindle_turning))
;;;4251                       settings->cycle_p SET_TO block->p_number;
;;;4252                   break;
;;;4253               case G_87:
;;;4254                   if (settings->motion_mode ISNT G_87)
;;;4255                   {
;;;4256                       CHK((block->i_flag IS OFF), NCE_I_WORD_MISSING_WITH_G87);

;;;4262                   k SET_TO block->k_flag IS ON ? block->k_number : settings->cycle_k;
;;;4263                   settings->cycle_i SET_TO i;
;;;4264                   settings->cycle_j SET_TO j;

;;;4266                   if (settings->distance_mode IS MODE_INCREMENTAL)
;;;4267                   {
;;;4268                       k SET_TO (cc + k);            /* k always absolute in function call below */
;;;4269                   }
;;;4270                   CYCLE_MACRO(convert_cycle_g87 (CANON_PLANE_XY, aa, (aa + i), bb,
;;;4271                       (bb + j), r, clear_cc, k, cc, settings->spindle_turning))
;;;4272                       break;
;;;4273               case G_88:
;;;4274                   CHK(((settings->motion_mode ISNT G_88) AND (block->p_number IS -1.0)),
;;;4275                       NCE_DWELL_TIME_P_WORD_MISSING_WITH_G88);
;;;4276                   block->p_number SET_TO
;;;4277                       block->p_number IS -1.0 ? settings->cycle_p : block->p_number;
;;;4278                   CYCLE_MACRO(convert_cycle_g88 (CANON_PLANE_XY, aa, bb, cc,

;;;4280                       settings->cycle_p SET_TO block->p_number;
;;;4281                   break;
;;;4282               case G_89:

;;;4285                   block->p_number SET_TO
;;;4286                       block->p_number IS -1.0 ? settings->cycle_p : block->p_number;

;;;4288                       block->p_number))
;;;4289                       settings->cycle_p SET_TO block->p_number;
;;;4290                   break;
;;;4291               default:

;;;4293           }
;;;4294           settings->current_x SET_TO aa;            /* CYCLE_MACRO updates aa and bb */
;;;4295           settings->current_y SET_TO bb;

;;;4297           settings->cycle_cc SET_TO block->z_number;

                  convert_cycle_yz PROC
;;;4353   
;;;4354       static int convert_cycle_yz(                  /* ARGUMENTS                                 */
000000  b507              PUSH     {r0-r2,lr}

;;;4367           double j;
;;;4368           double k;
;;;4369           double old_cc;

;;;4380                   NCE_X_VALUE_UNSPECIFIED_IN_YZ_PLANE_CANNED_CYCLE);
;;;4381           }
;;;4382           block->x_number SET_TO
;;;4383               block->x_flag IS ON ? block->x_number : settings->cycle_cc;
;;;4384           old_cc SET_TO settings->current_x;
;;;4385   
;;;4386           if (settings->distance_mode IS MODE_ABSOLUTE)
;;;4387           {
;;;4388               aa_increment SET_TO 0.0;
;;;4389               bb_increment SET_TO 0.0;
;;;4390               r SET_TO block->r_number;
;;;4391               cc SET_TO block->x_number;
;;;4392               aa SET_TO block->y_flag IS ON ? block->y_number : settings->current_y;

;;;4394           }
;;;4395           else if (settings->distance_mode IS MODE_INCREMENTAL)
;;;4396           {
;;;4397               aa_increment SET_TO block->y_number;
;;;4398               bb_increment SET_TO block->z_number;
;;;4399               r SET_TO (block->r_number + old_cc);
;;;4400               cc SET_TO (r + block->x_number);      /* [NCMS, page 98] */
;;;4401               aa SET_TO settings->current_y;
;;;4402               bb SET_TO settings->current_z;
;;;4403           }
;;;4404           else
;;;4405               ERM(NCE_BUG_DISTANCE_MODE_NOT_G90_OR_G91);
;;;4406           CHK((r < cc), NCE_R_LESS_THAN_X_IN_CYCLE_IN_YZ_PLANE);
;;;4407   
;;;4408           if (old_cc < r)
;;;4409           {
;;;4410               STRAIGHT_TRAVERSE(r, settings->current_y, settings->current_z
;;;4411       #ifdef AA
;;;4412                   ,      settings->AA_current
;;;4413       #else

;;;4416       #endif
;;;4417       #endif
;;;4418       #ifdef BB

;;;4420       #else
;;;4421       #ifdef ALL_AXES
;;;4422                   , 0
;;;4423       #endif
;;;4424       #endif
;;;4425       #ifdef CC
;;;4426                   ,  settings->CC_current
;;;4427       #else
;;;4428       #ifdef ALL_AXES
;;;4429                   , 0
;;;4430       #endif
;;;4431       #endif
;;;4432                   );
;;;4433               old_cc SET_TO r;
;;;4434           }
;;;4435           clear_cc SET_TO (settings->retract_mode IS R_PLANE) ? r : old_cc;
;;;4436   
;;;4437           save_mode = GET_EXTERNAL_MOTION_CONTROL_MODE();
;;;4438           if (save_mode ISNT CANON_EXACT_PATH)
;;;4439               SET_MOTION_CONTROL_MODE(CANON_EXACT_PATH);
;;;4440   
;;;4441           switch(motion)
;;;4442           {
;;;4443               case G_81:
;;;4444                   CYCLE_MACRO(convert_cycle_g81(CANON_PLANE_YZ, aa, bb, clear_cc, cc))
;;;4445                       break;
;;;4446               case G_82:
;;;4447                   CHK(((settings->motion_mode ISNT G_82) AND (block->p_number IS -1.0)),
;;;4448                       NCE_DWELL_TIME_P_WORD_MISSING_WITH_G82);
;;;4449                   block->p_number SET_TO
;;;4450                       block->p_number IS -1.0 ? settings->cycle_p : block->p_number;
;;;4451                   CYCLE_MACRO(convert_cycle_g82 (CANON_PLANE_YZ, aa, bb, clear_cc, cc,
;;;4452                       block->p_number))
;;;4453                       settings->cycle_p SET_TO block->p_number;
;;;4454                   break;
;;;4455               case G_83:
;;;4456                   CHK(((settings->motion_mode ISNT G_83) AND (block->q_number IS -1.0)),
;;;4457                       NCE_Q_WORD_MISSING_WITH_G83);
;;;4458                   block->q_number SET_TO
;;;4459                       block->q_number IS -1.0 ? settings->cycle_q : block->q_number;

;;;4461                       block->q_number))
;;;4462                       settings->cycle_q SET_TO block->q_number;
;;;4463                   break;
;;;4464               case G_84:
;;;4465                   CYCLE_MACRO(convert_cycle_g84 (CANON_PLANE_YZ, aa, bb, clear_cc, cc,
;;;4466                       settings->spindle_turning, settings->speed_feed_mode))
;;;4467                       break;
;;;4468               case G_85:
;;;4469                   CYCLE_MACRO(convert_cycle_g85 (CANON_PLANE_YZ, aa, bb, clear_cc, cc))
;;;4470                       break;
;;;4471               case G_86:
;;;4472                   CHK(((settings->motion_mode ISNT G_86) AND (block->p_number IS -1.0)),
;;;4473                       NCE_DWELL_TIME_P_WORD_MISSING_WITH_G86);
;;;4474                   block->p_number SET_TO
;;;4475                       block->p_number IS -1.0 ? settings->cycle_p : block->p_number;
;;;4476                   CYCLE_MACRO(convert_cycle_g86 (CANON_PLANE_YZ, aa, bb, clear_cc, cc,
;;;4477                       block->p_number, settings->spindle_turning))
;;;4478                       settings->cycle_p SET_TO block->p_number;
;;;4479                   break;
;;;4480               case G_87:
;;;4481                   if (settings->motion_mode ISNT G_87)
;;;4482                   {
;;;4483                       CHK((block->i_flag IS OFF), NCE_I_WORD_MISSING_WITH_G87);
;;;4484                       CHK((block->j_flag IS OFF), NCE_J_WORD_MISSING_WITH_G87);
;;;4485                       CHK((block->k_flag IS OFF), NCE_K_WORD_MISSING_WITH_G87);
;;;4486                   }
;;;4487                   i SET_TO block->i_flag IS ON ? block->i_number : settings->cycle_i;
;;;4488                   j SET_TO block->j_flag IS ON ? block->j_number : settings->cycle_j;
;;;4489                   k SET_TO block->k_flag IS ON ? block->k_number : settings->cycle_k;
;;;4490                   settings->cycle_i SET_TO i;
;;;4491                   settings->cycle_j SET_TO j;
;;;4492                   settings->cycle_k SET_TO k;
;;;4493                   if (settings->distance_mode IS MODE_INCREMENTAL)
;;;4494                   {
;;;4495                       i SET_TO (cc + i);            /* i always absolute in function call below */
;;;4496                   }
;;;4497                   CYCLE_MACRO(convert_cycle_g87 (CANON_PLANE_YZ, aa, (aa + j), bb,
;;;4498                       (bb + k), r, clear_cc, i, cc, settings->spindle_turning))
;;;4499                       break;
;;;4500               case G_88:
;;;4501                   CHK(((settings->motion_mode ISNT G_88) AND (block->p_number IS -1.0)),
;;;4502                       NCE_DWELL_TIME_P_WORD_MISSING_WITH_G88);
;;;4503                   block->p_number SET_TO
;;;4504                       block->p_number IS -1.0 ? settings->cycle_p : block->p_number;
;;;4505                   CYCLE_MACRO(convert_cycle_g88 (CANON_PLANE_YZ, aa, bb, cc,
;;;4506                       block->p_number, settings->spindle_turning))
;;;4507                       settings->cycle_p SET_TO block->p_number;
;;;4508                   break;
;;;4509               case G_89:
;;;4510                   CHK(((settings->motion_mode ISNT G_89) AND (block->p_number IS -1.0)),
;;;4511                       NCE_DWELL_TIME_P_WORD_MISSING_WITH_G89);
;;;4512                   block->p_number SET_TO
;;;4513                       block->p_number IS -1.0 ? settings->cycle_p : block->p_number;
;;;4514                   CYCLE_MACRO(convert_cycle_g89 (CANON_PLANE_YZ, aa, bb, clear_cc, cc,
;;;4515                       block->p_number))
;;;4516                       settings->cycle_p SET_TO block->p_number;
;;;4517                   break;
;;;4518               default:
;;;4519                   ERM(NCE_BUG_FUNCTION_SHOULD_NOT_HAVE_BEEN_CALLED);
;;;4520           }
;;;4521           settings->current_y SET_TO aa;            /* CYCLE_MACRO updates aa and bb */
;;;4522           settings->current_z SET_TO bb;
;;;4523           settings->current_x SET_TO clear_cc;
;;;4524           settings->cycle_cc SET_TO block->x_number;
;;;4525   
;;;4526           if (save_mode ISNT CANON_EXACT_PATH)
;;;4527               SET_MOTION_CONTROL_MODE(save_mode);
;;;4528   
;;;4529           return RS274NGC_OK;
;;;4530       }

                  convert_cycle_zx PROC
;;;4588   
;;;4589       static int convert_cycle_zx(                  /* ARGUMENTS                                 */
000000  b507              PUSH     {r0-r2,lr}
;;;4590       int motion,                                   /* a g-code between G_81 and G_89, a canned cycle */
;;;4591       block_pointer block,                          /* pointer to a block of RS274 instructions       */
;;;4592       setup_pointer settings)                       /* pointer to machine settings                    */
;;;4593       {
000002  b0b0              SUB      sp,sp,#0xc0
;;;4594           static char name[] SET_TO "convert_cycle_zx";
;;;4595           double aa;
;;;4596           double aa_increment;
;;;4597           double bb;
;;;4598           double bb_increment;
;;;4599           double cc;
;;;4600           double clear_cc;
;;;4601           double i;
;;;4602           double j;
;;;4603           double k;
;;;4604           double old_cc;
;;;4605           CANON_PLANE plane;
;;;4606           double r;
;;;4607           int repeat;
;;;4608           CANON_MOTION_MODE save_mode;
;;;4609           int status;
;;;4610   
;;;4611           plane SET_TO CANON_PLANE_XZ;
000004  f04f0003          MOV      r0,#3
000008  901b              STR      r0,[sp,#0x6c]
;;;4612           if (settings->motion_mode ISNT motion)
00000a  9832              LDR      r0,[sp,#0xc8]
00000c  f8d01628          LDR      r1,[r0,#0x628]
000010  9830              LDR      r0,[sp,#0xc0]
000012  4281              CMP      r1,r0
000014  d02a              BEQ      |L33.108|
;;;4613           {
;;;4614               CHK((block->y_flag IS OFF),
000016  9831              LDR      r0,[sp,#0xc4]

00001c  bb30              CBNZ     r0,|L33.108|
00001e  f04f0100          MOV      r1,#0
000022  48ff              LDR      r0,|L33.1056|
000024  f8c0114c          STR      r1,[r0,#0x14c]

000034  49fa              LDR      r1,|L33.1056|

00003e  f6a16154          SUB      r1,r1,#0xe54
000042  eb011000          ADD      r0,r1,r0,LSL #4
000046  49f7              LDR      r1,|L33.1060|

00005e  eb021000          ADD      r0,r2,r0,LSL #4
000062  7001              STRB     r1,[r0,#0]
000064  f04f00c2          MOV      r0,#0xc2
                  |L33.104|
;;;4615                   NCE_Y_VALUE_UNSPECIFIED_IN_XZ_PLANE_CANNED_CYCLE);
;;;4616           }
;;;4617           block->y_number SET_TO
;;;4618               block->y_flag IS ON ? block->y_number : settings->cycle_cc;
;;;4619           old_cc SET_TO settings->current_y;
;;;4620   
;;;4621           if (settings->distance_mode IS MODE_ABSOLUTE)
;;;4622           {
;;;4623               aa_increment SET_TO 0.0;
;;;4624               bb_increment SET_TO 0.0;
;;;4625               r SET_TO block->r_number;
;;;4626               cc SET_TO block->y_number;
;;;4627               aa SET_TO block->z_flag IS ON ? block->z_number : settings->current_z;
;;;4628               bb SET_TO block->x_flag IS ON ? block->x_number : settings->current_x;
;;;4629           }
;;;4630           else if (settings->distance_mode IS MODE_INCREMENTAL)
;;;4631           {
;;;4632               aa_increment SET_TO block->z_number;
;;;4633               bb_increment SET_TO block->x_number;
;;;4634               r SET_TO (block->r_number + old_cc);
;;;4635               cc SET_TO (r + block->y_number);      /* [NCMS, page 98] */
;;;4636               aa SET_TO settings->current_z;
;;;4637               bb SET_TO settings->current_x;
;;;4638           }
;;;4639           else
;;;4640               ERM(NCE_BUG_DISTANCE_MODE_NOT_G90_OR_G91);
;;;4641           CHK((r < cc), NCE_R_LESS_THAN_Y_IN_CYCLE_IN_XZ_PLANE);
;;;4642   
;;;4643           if (old_cc < r)
;;;4644           {
;;;4645               STRAIGHT_TRAVERSE(settings->current_x, r, settings->current_z
;;;4646       #ifdef AA
;;;4647                   ,           settings->AA_current
;;;4648       #else
;;;4649       #ifdef ALL_AXES
;;;4650                   , 0
;;;4651       #endif
;;;4652       #endif
;;;4653       #ifdef BB
;;;4654                   ,  settings->BB_current
;;;4655       #else
;;;4656       #ifdef ALL_AXES
;;;4657                   , 0
;;;4658       #endif
;;;4659       #endif
;;;4660       #ifdef CC
;;;4661                   ,  settings->CC_current
;;;4662       #else
;;;4663       #ifdef ALL_AXES
;;;4664                   , 0
;;;4665       #endif
;;;4666       #endif
;;;4667                   );
;;;4668               old_cc SET_TO r;
;;;4669           }
;;;4670           clear_cc SET_TO (settings->retract_mode IS R_PLANE) ? r : old_cc;
;;;4671   
;;;4672           save_mode = GET_EXTERNAL_MOTION_CONTROL_MODE();
;;;4673           if (save_mode ISNT CANON_EXACT_PATH)
;;;4674               SET_MOTION_CONTROL_MODE(CANON_EXACT_PATH);
;;;4675   
;;;4676           switch(motion)
;;;4677           {
;;;4678               case G_81:
;;;4679                   CYCLE_MACRO(convert_cycle_g81(CANON_PLANE_XZ, aa, bb, clear_cc, cc))
;;;4680                       break;
;;;4681               case G_82:
;;;4682                   CHK(((settings->motion_mode ISNT G_82) AND (block->p_number IS -1.0)),
;;;4683                       NCE_DWELL_TIME_P_WORD_MISSING_WITH_G82);
;;;4684                   block->p_number SET_TO
;;;4685                       block->p_number IS -1.0 ? settings->cycle_p : block->p_number;
;;;4686                   CYCLE_MACRO(convert_cycle_g82 (CANON_PLANE_XZ, aa, bb, clear_cc, cc,
;;;4687                       block->p_number))
;;;4688                       settings->cycle_p SET_TO block->p_number;
;;;4689                   break;
;;;4690               case G_83:
;;;4691                   CHK(((settings->motion_mode ISNT G_83) AND (block->q_number IS -1.0)),
;;;4692                       NCE_Q_WORD_MISSING_WITH_G83);
;;;4693                   block->q_number SET_TO
;;;4694                       block->q_number IS -1.0 ? settings->cycle_q : block->q_number;
;;;4695                   CYCLE_MACRO(convert_cycle_g83 (CANON_PLANE_XZ, aa, bb, r, clear_cc, cc,
;;;4696                       block->q_number))
;;;4697                       settings->cycle_q SET_TO block->q_number;
;;;4698                   break;
;;;4699               case G_84:
;;;4700                   CYCLE_MACRO(convert_cycle_g84 (CANON_PLANE_XZ, aa, bb, clear_cc, cc,
;;;4701                       settings->spindle_turning, settings->speed_feed_mode))
;;;4702                       break;
;;;4703               case G_85:
;;;4704                   CYCLE_MACRO(convert_cycle_g85 (CANON_PLANE_XZ, aa, bb, clear_cc, cc))
;;;4705                       break;
;;;4706               case G_86:
;;;4707                   CHK(((settings->motion_mode ISNT G_86) AND (block->p_number IS -1.0)),
;;;4708                       NCE_DWELL_TIME_P_WORD_MISSING_WITH_G86);
;;;4709                   block->p_number SET_TO
;;;4710                       block->p_number IS -1.0 ? settings->cycle_p : block->p_number;
;;;4711                   CYCLE_MACRO(convert_cycle_g86 (CANON_PLANE_XZ, aa, bb, clear_cc, cc,
;;;4712                       block->p_number, settings->spindle_turning))
;;;4713                       settings->cycle_p SET_TO block->p_number;
;;;4714                   break;
;;;4715               case G_87:
;;;4716                   if (settings->motion_mode ISNT G_87)
;;;4717                   {
;;;4718                       CHK((block->i_flag IS OFF), NCE_I_WORD_MISSING_WITH_G87);
;;;4719                       CHK((block->j_flag IS OFF), NCE_J_WORD_MISSING_WITH_G87);
;;;4720                       CHK((block->k_flag IS OFF), NCE_K_WORD_MISSING_WITH_G87);
;;;4721                   }
;;;4722                   i SET_TO block->i_flag IS ON ? block->i_number : settings->cycle_i;
;;;4723                   j SET_TO block->j_flag IS ON ? block->j_number : settings->cycle_j;
;;;4724                   k SET_TO block->k_flag IS ON ? block->k_number : settings->cycle_k;
;;;4725                   settings->cycle_i SET_TO i;
;;;4726                   settings->cycle_j SET_TO j;
;;;4727                   settings->cycle_k SET_TO k;
;;;4728                   if (settings->distance_mode IS MODE_INCREMENTAL)
;;;4729                   {
;;;4730                       j SET_TO (cc + j);            /* j always absolute in function call below */
;;;4731                   }
;;;4732                   CYCLE_MACRO(convert_cycle_g87 (CANON_PLANE_XZ, aa, (aa + k), bb,
;;;4733                       (bb + i), r, clear_cc, j, cc, settings->spindle_turning))
;;;4734                       break;
;;;4735               case G_88:
;;;4736                   CHK(((settings->motion_mode ISNT G_88) AND (block->p_number IS -1.0)),
;;;4737                       NCE_DWELL_TIME_P_WORD_MISSING_WITH_G88);
;;;4738                   block->p_number SET_TO
;;;4739                       block->p_number IS -1.0 ? settings->cycle_p : block->p_number;
;;;4740                   CYCLE_MACRO(convert_cycle_g88 (CANON_PLANE_XZ, aa, bb, cc,
;;;4741                       block->p_number, settings->spindle_turning))
;;;4742                       settings->cycle_p SET_TO block->p_number;
;;;4743                   break;

                  convert_speed PROC
;;;5967   
;;;5968       static int convert_speed(                     /* ARGUMENTS                                */
000000  b570              PUSH     {r4-r6,lr}
;;;5969       block_pointer block,                          /* pointer to a block of RS274 instructions */

;;;5971       {

                  convert_straight_comp1 PROC
;;;6518   
;;;6519       static int convert_straight_comp1(            /* ARGUMENTS                       */
000000  e92d4fff          PUSH     {r0-r11,lr}
;;;6520       int move,                                     /* either G_0 or G_1                         */
;;;6521       block_pointer block,                          /* pointer to a block of RS274 instructions  */
;;;6522       setup_pointer settings,                       /* pointer to machine settings               */
;;;6523       double px,                                    /* X coordinate of end point                 */

;;;6526   #ifdef AA
;;;6527       , double AA_end                               /* A coordinate of end point           *//*AA*/

;;;6536       {
000004  b08f              SUB      sp,sp,#0x3c
000006  4692              MOV      r10,r2
000008  e9dd891c          LDRD     r8,r9,[sp,#0x70]
;;;6537           static char name[] SET_TO "convert_straight_comp1";
;;;6538           double alpha;
;;;6539           double cx;                                /* first current point x then end point x */
;;;6540           double cy;                                /* first current point y then end point y */
;;;6541           double distance;
;;;6542           double radius;
;;;6543           int side;
;;;6544           double theta;
;;;6545   
;;;6546           side SET_TO settings->cutter_comp_side;

;;;6555           CHK((distance <= radius), NCE_CUTTER_GOUGING_WITH_CUTTER_RADIUS_COMP);
;;;6556   
;;;6557           theta SET_TO acos(radius/distance);
;;;6558           alpha SET_TO (side IS LEFT) ? (atan2((cy - py), (cx - px)) - theta) :
;;;6559           (atan2((cy - py), (cx - px)) + theta);
;;;6560           cx SET_TO (px + (radius * cos(alpha)));   /* reset to end location */
;;;6561           cy SET_TO (py + (radius * sin(alpha)));
;;;6562           if (move IS G_0)
;;;6563               STRAIGHT_TRAVERSE(cx, cy, end_z
;;;6564           #ifdef AA

;;;6583           #endif

;;;6607       #ifdef ALL_AXES

;;;6609       #endif
;;;6610       #endif
;;;6611       #ifdef BB

;;;6613       #else
;;;6614       #ifdef ALL_AXES

;;;6616       #endif
;;;6617       #endif
;;;6618       #ifdef CC

;;;6620       #else
;;;6621       #ifdef ALL_AXES
;;;6622                   , 0
;;;6623       #endif
;;;6624       #endif
;;;6625                   );
;;;6626           }
;;;6627           else
;;;6628               ERM(NCE_BUG_CODE_NOT_G0_OR_G1);
;;;6629   
;;;6630           settings->current_x SET_TO cx;
;;;6631           settings->current_y SET_TO cy;
;;;6632           settings->program_x SET_TO px;
;;;6633           settings->program_y SET_TO py;
;;;6634           return RS274NGC_OK;
;;;6635       }

;;;6708   
;;;6709       static int convert_straight_comp2(            /* ARGUMENTS                       */
000000  e92d4fff          PUSH     {r0-r11,lr}
;;;6710       int move,                                     /* either G_0 or G_1                         */

;;;6826               {

                          AREA ||i.enhance_block||, CODE, READONLY, ALIGN=2

                  enhance_block PROC
;;;7419   
;;;7420       static int enhance_block(                     /* ARGUMENTS                         */
000000  e92d41f0          PUSH     {r4-r8,lr}
;;;7421       block_pointer block,                          /* pointer to a block to be checked  */
;;;7422       setup_pointer settings)                       /* pointer to machine settings       */
;;;7423       {
000004  4604              MOV      r4,r0
000006  460e              MOV      r6,r1
;;;7424           static char name[] SET_TO "enhance_block";
;;;7425           int axis_flag;
;;;7426           int mode_zero_covets_axes;
;;;7427   
;;;7428           axis_flag SET_TO ((block->x_flag IS ON) OR
000008  f8d401dc          LDR      r0,[r4,#0x1dc]
00000c  2801              CMP      r0,#1
00000e  d007              BEQ      |L58.32|
;;;7429               (block->y_flag IS ON) OR
000010  f8d401e8          LDR      r0,[r4,#0x1e8]
000014  2801              CMP      r0,#1
000016  d003              BEQ      |L58.32|
;;;7430       #ifdef AA
;;;7431               (block->a_flag IS ON) OR              /*AA*/
;;;7432       #endif
;;;7433       #ifdef BB
;;;7434               (block->b_flag IS ON) OR              /*BB*/

                          AREA ||i.find_arc_length||, CODE, READONLY, ALIGN=1

                  find_arc_length PROC
;;;7832   
;;;7833       static double find_arc_length(                /* ARGUMENTS                          */
000000  e92d4ff0          PUSH     {r4-r11,lr}
;;;7834       double x1,                                    /* X-coordinate of start point        */
;;;7835       double y1,                                    /* Y-coordinate of start point        */
;;;7836       double z1,                                    /* Z-coordinate of start point        */
;;;7837       double center_x,                              /* X-coordinate of arc center         */
;;;7838       double center_y,                              /* Y-coordinate of arc center         */
;;;7839       int turn,                                     /* no. of full or partial circles CCW */
;;;7840       double x2,                                    /* X-coordinate of end point          */
;;;7841       double y2,                                    /* Y-coordinate of end point          */
;;;7842       double z2)                                    /* Z-coordinate of end point          */
;;;7843       {
000004  b08d              SUB      sp,sp,#0x34
000006  4606              MOV      r6,r0
000008  460f              MOV      r7,r1
00000a  4690              MOV      r8,r2
00000c  4699              MOV      r9,r3
00000e  e9ddab18          LDRD     r10,r11,[sp,#0x60]
;;;7844           double radius;
;;;7845           double theta;                             /* amount of turn of arc in radians */
;;;7846   
;;;7847           radius SET_TO hypot((center_x - x1), (center_y - y1));
000012  4642              MOV      r2,r8
000014  464b              MOV      r3,r9
000016  e9dd011a          LDRD     r0,r1,[sp,#0x68]
00001a  f7fffffe          BL       __aeabi_dsub
00001e  4652              MOV      r2,r10
000020  465b              MOV      r3,r11
000022  e9cd0108          STRD     r0,r1,[sp,#0x20]
000026  4630              MOV      r0,r6
000028  4639              MOV      r1,r7
00002a  f7fffffe          BL       __aeabi_drsub
00002e  e9cd0106          STRD     r0,r1,[sp,#0x18]
000032  e9dd2308          LDRD     r2,r3,[sp,#0x20]
000036  f7fffffe          BL       hypot
00003a  e9cd010a          STRD     r0,r1,[sp,#0x28]
;;;7848           theta SET_TO find_turn(x1, y1, center_x, center_y, turn, x2, y2);
00003e  e9dd0120          LDRD     r0,r1,[sp,#0x80]
000042  e9cd0108          STRD     r0,r1,[sp,#0x20]
000046  e9dd011e          LDRD     r0,r1,[sp,#0x78]
00004a  e9cd0106          STRD     r0,r1,[sp,#0x18]
00004e  981c              LDR      r0,[sp,#0x70]
000050  9004              STR      r0,[sp,#0x10]
000052  e9dd011a          LDRD     r0,r1,[sp,#0x68]
000056  4642              MOV      r2,r8
000058  464b              MOV      r3,r9
00005a  e9cdab00          STRD     r10,r11,[sp,#0]
00005e  e9cd0102          STRD     r0,r1,[sp,#8]
000062  4630              MOV      r0,r6
000064  4639              MOV      r1,r7
000066  f7fffffe          BL       find_turn
00006a  4604              MOV      r4,r0
00006c  460d              MOV      r5,r1
;;;7849           if (z2 IS z1)
00006e  e9dd2316          LDRD     r2,r3,[sp,#0x58]
000072  e9dd0122          LDRD     r0,r1,[sp,#0x88]
000076  f7fffffe          BL       __aeabi_cdcmpeq
00007a  d10b              BNE      |L64.148|
;;;7850               return (radius * fabs(theta));
00007c  f0254000          BIC      r0,r5,#0x80000000
000080  e9cd4008          STRD     r4,r0,[sp,#0x20]
000084  4620              MOV      r0,r4
000086  a909              ADD      r1,sp,#0x24
000088  c90e              LDM      r1,{r1-r3}
00008a  f7fffffe          BL       __aeabi_dmul
                  |L64.142|
;;;7851           else
;;;7852               return hypot((radius * theta), (z2 - z1));
;;;7853       }
00008e  b00d              ADD      sp,sp,#0x34
000090  e8bd8ff0          POP      {r4-r11,pc}
                  |L64.148|
000094  e9dd2316          LDRD     r2,r3,[sp,#0x58]      ;7852
000098  e9dd0122          LDRD     r0,r1,[sp,#0x88]      ;7852
00009c  f7fffffe          BL       __aeabi_dsub
0000a0  4622              MOV      r2,r4                 ;7852
0000a2  462b              MOV      r3,r5                 ;7852
0000a4  e9cd0108          STRD     r0,r1,[sp,#0x20]      ;7852
0000a8  e9dd010a          LDRD     r0,r1,[sp,#0x28]      ;7852
0000ac  f7fffffe          BL       __aeabi_dmul
0000b0  e9cd0106          STRD     r0,r1,[sp,#0x18]      ;7852
0000b4  e9dd2308          LDRD     r2,r3,[sp,#0x20]      ;7852
0000b8  f7fffffe          BL       hypot
0000bc  e7e7              B        |L64.142|
;;;7854   
                          ENDP


                          AREA ||i.find_ends||, CODE, READONLY, ALIGN=2

                  find_ends PROC
;;;7894   
;;;7895       static int find_ends(                         /* ARGUMENTS                                    */
000000  e92d4ff0          PUSH     {r4-r11,lr}

                  |L65.52|

;;;8192               ))                                    /* straight line */

                  find_turn PROC
;;;8221   
;;;8222       static double find_turn(                      /* ARGUMENTS                          */
000000  e92d47ff          PUSH     {r0-r10,lr}
;;;8223       double x1,                                    /* X-coordinate of start point        */
;;;8224       double y1,                                    /* Y-coordinate of start point        */
;;;8225       double center_x,                              /* X-coordinate of arc center         */
;;;8226       double center_y,                              /* Y-coordinate of arc center         */
;;;8227       int turn,                                     /* no. of full or partial circles CCW */
;;;8228       double x2,                                    /* X-coordinate of end point          */
;;;8229       double y2)                                    /* Y-coordinate of end point          */
;;;8230       {
000004  b086              SUB      sp,sp,#0x18
000006  f8dda058          LDR      r10,[sp,#0x58]
;;;8231           double alpha;                             /* angle of first radius                      */
;;;8232           double beta;                              /* angle of second radius                     */
;;;8233           double theta;                             /* amount of turn of arc CCW - negative if CW */
;;;8234   
;;;8235           if (turn IS 0)

;;;8236               return 0.0;
000010  2000              MOVS     r0,#0
000012  4601              MOV      r1,r0
                  |L68.20|

;;;8238           beta SET_TO atan2((y2 - center_y), (x2 - center_x));
;;;8239           if (turn > 0)
;;;8240           {
;;;8241               if (beta <= alpha)
;;;8242                   beta SET_TO (beta + TWO_PI);
;;;8243               theta SET_TO ((beta - alpha) + ((turn - 1) * TWO_PI));
;;;8244           }
;;;8245           else                                      /* turn < 0 */
;;;8246           {
;;;8247               if (alpha <= beta)
;;;8248                   alpha SET_TO (alpha + TWO_PI);

;;;8250           }

;;;8354

                  precedence PROC

;;;8640       int an_operator)
;;;8641       {
;;;8642           if (an_operator IS RIGHT_BRACKET)

                  |L75.8|

;;;8645               return 4;

;;;8649               return 3;
;;;8650       }

                  |L75.10|

                  |L75.26|
00001a  2003              MOVS     r0,#3                 ;8649
00001c  e7f4              B        |L75.8|

                          ENDP

                          AREA ||i.write_m_codes||, CODE, READONLY, ALIGN=1

                  write_m_codes PROC
;;;11438  
;;;11439      static int write_m_codes(                     /* ARGUMENTS                                    */
000000  4603              MOV      r3,r0
;;;11440      block_pointer block,                          /* pointer to a block of RS274/NGC instructions */
;;;11441      setup_pointer settings)                       /* pointer to machine settings                  */
;;;11442      {
;;;11443          int * emz;
;;;11444  
;;;11445          emz SET_TO settings->active_m_codes;
000002  f1010030          ADD      r0,r1,#0x30
000006  4602              MOV      r2,r0
;;;11446          emz[0] SET_TO settings->sequence_number;  /* 0 seq number  */
000008  f24b1090          MOV      r0,#0xb190
00000c  5840              LDR      r0,[r0,r1]
00000e  6010              STR      r0,[r2,#0]
;;;11447          emz[1] SET_TO
000010  b913              CBNZ     r3,|L134.24|
;;;11448              (block IS NULL) ? -1 : block->m_modes[4];/* 1 stopping    */
000012  f04f30ff          MOV      r0,#0xffffffff
000016  e002              B        |L134.30|
                  |L134.24|
000018  f44f70cc          MOV      r0,#0x198
00001c  58c0              LDR      r0,[r0,r3]
                  |L134.30|
00001e  6050              STR      r0,[r2,#4]
;;;11449          emz[2] SET_TO
000020  f24b10a8          MOV      r0,#0xb1a8
000024  5840              LDR      r0,[r0,r1]
000026  2801              CMP      r0,#1
000028  d102              BNE      |L134.48|
;;;11450     /* 2 spindle     */
;;;11451              (settings->spindle_turning IS CANON_STOPPED) ? 5 :
00002a  f04f0005          MOV      r0,#5
00002e  e009              B        |L134.68|
                  |L134.48|
;;;11452          (settings->spindle_turning IS CANON_CLOCKWISE) ? 3 : 4;
000030  f24b10a8          MOV      r0,#0xb1a8
000034  5840              LDR      r0,[r0,r1]
000036  2802              CMP      r0,#2
000038  d102              BNE      |L134.64|
00003a  f04f0003          MOV      r0,#3
00003e  e001              B        |L134.68|
                  |L134.64|
000040  f04f0004          MOV      r0,#4
                  |L134.68|
000044  6090              STR      r0,[r2,#8]
;;;11453          emz[3] SET_TO                             /* 3 tool change */
000046  b913              CBNZ     r3,|L134.78|
;;;11454              (block IS NULL) ? -1 : block->m_modes[6];
000048  f04f30ff          MOV      r0,#0xffffffff
00004c  e002              B        |L134.84|
                  |L134.78|
00004e  f44f70d0          MOV      r0,#0x1a0
000052  58c0              LDR      r0,[r0,r3]
                  |L134.84|
000054  60d0              STR      r0,[r2,#0xc]
;;;11455          emz[4] SET_TO                             /* 4 mist        */
000056  f8d10624          LDR      r0,[r1,#0x624]
00005a  2801              CMP      r0,#1
00005c  d102              BNE      |L134.100|
;;;11456              (settings->mist IS ON) ? 7 :
00005e  f04f0007          MOV      r0,#7
000062  e008              B        |L134.118|
                  |L134.100|
;;;11457          (settings->flood IS ON) ? -1 : 9;
000064  f8d10514          LDR      r0,[r1,#0x514]
000068  2801              CMP      r0,#1
00006a  d102              BNE      |L134.114|
00006c  f04f30ff          MOV      r0,#0xffffffff
000070  e001              B        |L134.118|
                  |L134.114|
000072  f04f0009          MOV      r0,#9
                  |L134.118|
000076  6110              STR      r0,[r2,#0x10]
;;;11458          emz[5] SET_TO                             /* 5 flood       */
000078  f8d10514          LDR      r0,[r1,#0x514]
00007c  2801              CMP      r0,#1
00007e  d102              BNE      |L134.134|
;;;11459              (settings->flood IS ON) ? 8 : -1;
000080  f04f0008          MOV      r0,#8
000084  e001              B        |L134.138|
                  |L134.134|
000086  f04f30ff          MOV      r0,#0xffffffff
                  |L134.138|
00008a  6150              STR      r0,[r2,#0x14]
;;;11460          emz[6] SET_TO                             /* 6 overrides   */

000090  2801              CMP      r0,#1
000092  d102              BNE      |L134.154|
;;;11461              (settings->feed_override IS ON) ? 48 : 49;
000094  f04f0030          MOV      r0,#0x30
000098  e001              B        |L134.158|
                  |L134.154|
00009a  f04f0031          MOV      r0,#0x31
                  |L134.158|
00009e  6190              STR      r0,[r2,#0x18]
;;;11462  
;;;11463          return RS274NGC_OK;
0000a0  2000              MOVS     r0,#0
;;;11464      }
0000a2  4770              BX       lr
;;;11465  
                          ENDP


                          AREA ||i.write_settings||, CODE, READONLY, ALIGN=1

                  write_settings PROC
;;;11481  
;;;11482      static int write_settings(                    /* ARGUMENTS                   */
000000  b570              PUSH     {r4-r6,lr}
;;;11483      setup_pointer settings)                       /* pointer to machine settings */
;;;11484      {
000002  4604              MOV      r4,r0
;;;11485          double * vals;
;;;11486  
;;;11487          vals SET_TO settings->active_settings;
000004  f1040050          ADD      r0,r4,#0x50
000008  4605              MOV      r5,r0
;;;11488          vals[0] SET_TO settings->sequence_number; /* 0 sequence number */
00000a  f24b1190          MOV      r1,#0xb190
00000e  5909              LDR      r1,[r1,r4]
000010  4608              MOV      r0,r1
000012  f7fffffe          BL       __aeabi_i2d
000016  e9c50100          STRD     r0,r1,[r5,#0]
;;;11489          vals[1] SET_TO settings->feed_rate;       /* 1 feed rate       */
00001a  f5046081          ADD      r0,r4,#0x408
00001e  c803              LDM      r0,{r0,r1}
000020  e9c50102          STRD     r0,r1,[r5,#8]
;;;11490          vals[2] SET_TO settings->speed;           /* 2 spindle speed   */
000024  f5044030          ADD      r0,r4,#0xb000
000028  f50070cc          ADD      r0,r0,#0x198
00002c  c803              LDM      r0,{r0,r1}
00002e  e9c50104          STRD     r0,r1,[r5,#0x10]
;;;11491  
;;;11492          return RS274NGC_OK;
000032  f04f0000          MOV      r0,#0
;;;11493      }
000036  bd70              POP      {r4-r6,pc}
;;;11494  
                          ENDP
